496
00:32:36,288 --> 00:32:38,131
Oh, I'm so sorry.

497
00:32:38,206 --> 00:32:39,503
I'm dreadfully sorry.

498
00:32:39,624 --> 00:32:41,547
Yes?
Sorry.

499
00:32:41,626 --> 00:32:43,720
I'm just looking
for this address.

500
00:32:46,214 --> 00:32:48,057
Yes.
Do you understand?

501
00:32:48,133 --> 00:32:49,760
Could you help me
find this place?

502
00:32:49,843 --> 00:32:51,345
Yes.

503
00:32:51,428 --> 00:32:55,558
Is that, yes, you do understand
or, yes, you could help me?

504
00:32:55,682 --> 00:32:58,105
Yes. Yes.
Oh.

505
00:32:58,185 --> 00:33:00,608
Well, let's just
go with both, shall we?

506
00:33:00,687 --> 00:33:01,939
Yes.

507
00:33:09,905 --> 00:33:11,407
Oh!

508
00:33:23,835 --> 00:33:25,553
Yes.

509
00:33:34,888 --> 00:33:36,606
Give me the ball.

510
00:33:36,723 --> 00:33:39,476
I can take him.

511
00:33:39,559 --> 00:33:42,563
Down is where
you are going, uncle.

512
00:33:42,646 --> 00:33:44,319
You do your worst.

513
00:33:53,490 --> 00:33:54,992
Come on, Sanjay.
You can do it.

514
00:33:55,075 --> 00:33:56,543
Come on, Sanjay.

515
00:34:08,964 --> 00:34:12,434
I felt the need,
the need for speed.

516
00:34:12,509 --> 00:34:13,761
Yes!

517
00:34:17,013 --> 00:34:18,981
Are you all right, uncle?

518
00:34:20,267 --> 00:34:22,486
Yes. Yes, I'm fine.

519
00:34:35,615 --> 00:34:37,117
Oh.

520
00:34:43,373 --> 00:34:46,547
We do appreciate your custom,
which is very important to us.

521
00:34:46,626 --> 00:34:49,505
And can I draw your attention
to our special new-

522
00:34:57,220 --> 00:34:59,314
Are you sure I can't
offer you something?

523
00:34:59,389 --> 00:35:02,984
We have some, uh, English breakfast
tea, Building tea, as you call it.

524
00:35:03,059 --> 00:35:05,562
A builder's tea?
Builder's tea.

525
00:35:05,645 --> 00:35:07,113
No, thank you. I'm fine.

526
00:35:07,188 --> 00:35:08,815
So, tell me. How can I help you?

527
00:35:08,898 --> 00:35:12,027
I don't think you can. I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have come.

528
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:13,532
No, wait.

529
00:35:13,612 --> 00:35:15,990
It's just that I saw your
advertisement in the local newspaper,

530
00:35:16,072 --> 00:35:19,201
and it specifically mentioned the
ability to talk to older people.

531
00:35:19,284 --> 00:35:22,709
But this wasn't
what I imagined.

532
00:35:22,787 --> 00:35:25,336
- You came for a job?
- I'm sorry. I've wasted your time.

533
00:35:25,415 --> 00:35:29,795
Look, everyone working here is a
graduate from a good university.

534
00:35:29,878 --> 00:35:33,052
This is a place for ambitious
people, young people.

535
00:35:33,131 --> 00:35:34,724
Yes, I see that now.
I'm sorry.

536
00:35:34,799 --> 00:35:36,517
No. Please, sit down.

537
00:35:36,593 --> 00:35:38,812
Sit down. Please.

538
00:35:42,641 --> 00:35:44,393
So it is really builder's tea?

539
00:35:45,393 --> 00:35:48,772
Yes. We dunk biscuits
into it.

540
00:35:48,855 --> 00:35:50,357
You dunk?

541
00:35:51,941 --> 00:35:55,115
Well, it means lowering the
biscuit into the tea...

542
00:35:55,195 --> 00:35:57,493
and letting it
soak in there."

543
00:35:57,572 --> 00:36:01,076
and trying to calculate the exact
moment before the biscuit dissolves...

544
00:36:01,159 --> 00:36:03,378
when you can whip it up
into your mouth...

545
00:36:03,453 --> 00:36:06,798
and enjoy the blissful union
of biscuit and tea combined.

546
00:36:09,334 --> 00:36:10,961
It is more relaxing
than it sounds,

547
00:36:12,796 --> 00:36:14,764
Perhaps you can
help us after all.

548
00:36:25,100 --> 00:36:26,773
I thought
you weren't coming.

549
00:36:26,851 --> 00:36:28,524
Have I ever let you down?

550
00:36:28,603 --> 00:36:31,152
Um-
Don't answer that.

551
00:36:33,441 --> 00:36:34,738
I have to go.

552
00:36:34,818 --> 00:36:36,491
Leave this place.
Come to work for me.

553
00:36:36,569 --> 00:36:38,321
You can't afford me.

554
00:36:38,405 --> 00:36:39,952
I can't afford anything.

555
00:36:40,031 --> 00:36:41,157
I miss you.

556
00:36:41,241 --> 00:36:43,118
Am I coming round tonight?

557
00:36:43,201 --> 00:36:46,330
Uh, let's meet somewhere else.
I will rent a hotel room.

558
00:36:46,413 --> 00:36:49,383
Sonny, you own a hotel.
It has many rooms.

559
00:36:49,457 --> 00:36:53,337
Some of which are now occupied
with actual real guests.

560
00:36:53,420 --> 00:36:55,138
Paying guests?

561
00:36:55,213 --> 00:36:58,137
Why must you nitpick?
It is not an attractive quality.

562
00:37:01,344 --> 00:37:02,470
Sunaina.

563
00:37:04,055 --> 00:37:05,523
Hello, Jay.

564
00:37:05,598 --> 00:37:06,724
Sonny boy.

565
00:37:06,808 --> 00:37:08,560
Don't call me that.

566
00:37:08,643 --> 00:37:11,613
If you're gonna mess around with
my sister, don't do it in public.

567
00:37:12,105 --> 00:37:13,482
Let's go.

568
00:37:30,206 --> 00:37:31,879
Good evening, Your Honor.

569
00:37:33,334 --> 00:37:36,213
Ah, good evening, Mrs. Ainslie.
You have a good day?

570
00:37:36,296 --> 00:37:38,173
What did you get up to?

571
00:37:38,256 --> 00:37:40,350
Well, I started
in my bedroom,

572
00:37:40,425 --> 00:37:43,725
where I spent a happy couple of hours
giving all the cockroaches names.

573
00:37:43,803 --> 00:37:48,058
And then, after a lunch that will
long have a place in my heartburn,

574
00:37:48,141 --> 00:37:50,769
I came out here
and stared blindly at a book,

575
00:37:50,852 --> 00:37:53,901
waiting for someone-
anyone- to rescue me.

576
00:37:55,190 --> 00:37:58,069
And how glad I am
it was you.

577
00:37:58,151 --> 00:38:00,529
Why would you not go out?
There's so much to see.

578
00:38:01,780 --> 00:38:04,750
All life is here, Mrs. Ainslie.
I tell you.

579
00:38:07,577 --> 00:38:10,046
Oh, I could have a word
with the chef if you like,

580
00:38:10,121 --> 00:38:13,170
Perhaps some grilled chicken
and plain rice?

581
00:38:13,249 --> 00:38:15,251
That would be
much appreciated.

582
00:38:16,377 --> 00:38:17,424
All right.

583
00:38:54,541 --> 00:38:56,009
Good evening.

584
00:38:56,084 --> 00:38:57,256
Good evening.

585
00:38:57,377 --> 00:39:00,051
Please. Please, sit down.
Oh.

586
00:39:00,129 --> 00:39:01,130
Thank you.

587
00:39:01,214 --> 00:39:03,057
I trust you had
a good day.

588
00:39:03,132 --> 00:39:05,260
I'd rather hear about yours.

589
00:39:05,343 --> 00:39:08,267
I got a job-
my first ever.

590
00:39:08,346 --> 00:39:10,690
I'm going to be a sort of
cultural adviser.

591
00:39:10,765 --> 00:39:14,520
A role I'm sure you'll perform
with great distinction.

592
00:39:14,602 --> 00:39:17,446
Perhaps you wouldn't
mind keeping that to yourself.

593
00:39:17,522 --> 00:39:20,526
Well, I-I-I'm flattered
you told me about it.

594
00:39:20,608 --> 00:39:22,030
Good evening, the Ainslies.

595
00:39:22,151 --> 00:39:24,870
Did you have a good day?
Spectacular actually.

596
00:39:24,988 --> 00:39:29,209
I went to the temple you told me about,
a place of meditation and peace.

597
00:39:29,284 --> 00:39:30,957
It was quite stunning.

598
00:39:31,035 --> 00:39:33,834
So spiritual, I bet you never
noticed the smell of elephant dung.

599
00:39:33,913 --> 00:39:36,712
No elephants, sadly.

600
00:39:36,791 --> 00:39:39,169
I thought I might see you there.
Where did you get to instead?

601
00:39:39,252 --> 00:39:41,471
Yes, where do you
get to every day?

602
00:39:41,546 --> 00:39:44,390
Well, I-I've just been telling
Mrs. Greenslade all about it.

603
00:39:44,465 --> 00:39:46,217
I'm sure she wouldn't
mind hearing it again.

604
00:39:46,301 --> 00:39:50,147
Oh, I talked to the chef for you.
Absolutely no problem.

605
00:39:50,221 --> 00:39:51,894
Did you hear that, Douglas?

606
00:39:51,973 --> 00:39:54,692
Plain grilled food,
Manna from heaven.

607
00:39:54,809 --> 00:39:57,779
I don't have Io have it too, do I?
I can't thank you enough.

608
00:39:57,854 --> 00:39:59,572
You really should
see this temple.

609
00:39:59,647 --> 00:40:01,274
Oh, I'd like to very much.

610
00:40:01,357 --> 00:40:03,860
But maybe take
a clothes-peg for your nose.

611
00:40:09,490 --> 00:40:11,663
Good night.
Good night.

612
00:40:14,245 --> 00:40:15,918
Um, Mrs. Greenslade?

613
00:40:17,040 --> 00:40:18,508
Evelyn.

614
00:40:20,043 --> 00:40:22,717
Would you mind
if I showed you something?

615
00:40:24,589 --> 00:40:27,388
I grew up here,
just a short drive away.

616
00:40:28,676 --> 00:40:31,099
It was a big house.
We had servants.

617
00:40:31,179 --> 00:40:34,308
Oh, we knew their wives
and children, and...

618
00:40:34,390 --> 00:40:37,610
one of the boys, uh, Manoj-

619
00:40:37,685 --> 00:40:39,232
Oh.

620
00:40:41,314 --> 00:40:43,191
He, um-
He became my friend.

621
00:40:44,484 --> 00:40:47,863
And, uh, we played lots
of cricket together, and-

622
00:40:47,946 --> 00:40:52,873
Well, we played everything together, and-and
it stayed like that for a few years.

623
00:40:52,951 --> 00:40:54,168
And then, um-

624
00:40:55,119 --> 00:40:58,123
And then one night, it, uh-

625
00:40:58,206 --> 00:41:01,050
it became something else.

626
00:41:04,045 --> 00:41:06,139
We had a few months together.
We had that.

627
00:41:06,214 --> 00:41:09,434
And, um- And then there was
a weekend in Udaipur...

628
00:41:09,509 --> 00:41:15,187
where... we were sitting by a lake
and watching the sun go down.

629
00:41:15,264 --> 00:41:20,316
And, uh, I remember thinking that I-I
would never be this happy again.

630
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:26,110
And- And I was right.

631
00:41:26,192 --> 00:41:28,866
Because, suddenly,
it was over.

632
00:41:28,945 --> 00:41:32,245
We'd fallen asleep,
and they found us.

633
00:41:33,992 --> 00:41:36,165
Well, it was bad enough
for me.

634
00:41:36,244 --> 00:41:39,498
But I knew who I was, and I
think my family guessed.

635
00:41:39,580 --> 00:41:41,332
But for-

636
00:41:41,416 --> 00:41:46,673
for Manoj, the-
the disgrace was absolute.

637
00:41:46,754 --> 00:41:50,304
His father was fired.
His family was sent away, all of them.

638
00:41:52,844 --> 00:41:55,063
And, uh,

639
00:41:55,138 --> 00:41:57,140
well, I don't know
what I could have done.

640
00:41:57,223 --> 00:41:59,942
But it should have been
more than nothing.

641
00:42:00,018 --> 00:42:03,113
I just-
I just let it happen.

642
00:42:03,187 --> 00:42:07,112
I didn't put up
any kind of a tight. I-

643
00:42:09,027 --> 00:42:11,121
And then, um-

644
00:42:11,195 --> 00:42:13,914
Then I went back to England,
to-to-to university.

645
00:42:14,032 --> 00:42:19,960
And, uh, I always said, you know, I'm
going to go back. I shall go back.

646
00:42:22,206 --> 00:42:24,584
And I never did.

647
00:42:25,501 --> 00:42:27,174
Until now.

648
00:42:29,255 --> 00:42:31,132
Until now.

649
00:42:32,508 --> 00:42:34,602
And now I think-

650
00:42:36,304 --> 00:42:40,150
What if I'm the last person in
the world that he wants to see?

651
00:42:41,851 --> 00:42:44,479
Do you want to see him?
Yes.

652
00:42:47,023 --> 00:42:49,025
Yes, yes.

653
00:42:49,942 --> 00:42:52,070
Then you must.

654
00:43:47,250 --> 00:43:49,878
So now that we are
fully operational, Mr. Maruthi,

655
00:43:50,002 --> 00:43:53,597
it is clear that, with a small injection
of funds for the phase two development,

656
00:43:53,673 --> 00:43:57,723
The Best Exotic Marigold Hotel
can rise like a phoenix...

657
00:43:57,802 --> 00:43:59,850
to its previous stale of glory.

658
00:43:59,929 --> 00:44:02,432
And, look,
when I say small injection,

659
00:44:02,515 --> 00:44:05,394
I mean small in the sense
of, uh, medium-sized.

660
00:44:05,476 --> 00:44:10,528
- Possibly larger.
- Well, this hotel was never glorious.

661
00:44:10,606 --> 00:44:12,950
Just the phoenix part then.

662
00:44:13,067 --> 00:44:15,320
How many rooms will there be?
Many. Mmm.

663
00:44:15,403 --> 00:44:17,121
How many?
A great amount.

664
00:44:17,196 --> 00:44:18,823
Plenty of rooms.
No question.

665
00:44:18,948 --> 00:44:21,918
I'm not a details man, Mr.
Maruthi. Nor was your father.

666
00:44:21,993 --> 00:44:25,668
Mr. Maruthi, I present to you
one of our beloved guests.

667
00:44:25,746 --> 00:44:27,248
Dear Mrs. Donnelly,

668
00:44:27,331 --> 00:44:30,710
please can you describe to us in
as much detail as you desire...

669
00:44:30,793 --> 00:44:34,297
your experience of the
ambience and atmosphere."

670
00:44:34,380 --> 00:44:36,974
of The Best Exotic
Marigold Hotel.

671
00:44:38,718 --> 00:44:40,220
Words fail me.

672
00:44:44,307 --> 00:44:48,232
Ah, the English wit
we love so greatly.

673
00:44:48,311 --> 00:44:49,813
Thank you, madam.

674
00:44:49,896 --> 00:44:54,276
See, the wheel is spinning, but,
you know, the hamster is dead.

675
00:44:54,358 --> 00:44:58,488
- Mummyji what are you doing here?
- You called. I came.

676
00:44:58,571 --> 00:45:00,824
No, I couldn't have called.
The phones don't work.

677
00:45:00,907 --> 00:45:04,081
That's why I came.

678
00:45:06,037 --> 00:45:09,712
- Wait! Mummyji this is my office!
- Who is that man out there?

679
00:45:09,790 --> 00:45:12,339
The contents of that desk are mine.
Do not open the drawers.

680
00:45:12,418 --> 00:45:15,012
I must insist that you
do not open the drawers.

681
00:45:15,087 --> 00:45:16,384
Tell me.
Why have you come?

682
00:45:16,464 --> 00:45:18,558
Do I need a reason
to visit my favorite son?

683
00:45:18,674 --> 00:45:22,019
No. He's in his mansion in Delhi.
All right. My second favorite.

684
00:45:22,094 --> 00:45:23,687
He went to Canada
to make his fortune.

685
00:45:23,763 --> 00:45:27,063
- And make it, he did.
- As I will make mine!

686
00:45:27,141 --> 00:45:30,020
I have a dream, Mummyji.
A most brilliant one.

687
00:45:30,102 --> 00:45:33,151
To outsource old age.
And it is not just for the British.

688
00:45:33,272 --> 00:45:36,276
There are many other countries where
they don't like old people too.

689
00:45:36,359 --> 00:45:39,704
Sonny, your brothers own
one-third of this hotel each.

690
00:45:39,779 --> 00:45:42,407
They're also entitled to
one-third of the profits, no?

691
00:45:42,490 --> 00:45:45,744
Success does not
happen overnight, Mummyji.

692
00:45:45,868 --> 00:45:50,999
This is blue-sky thinking, and it requires
long-term strategy and-and-and patience.

693
00:45:51,082 --> 00:45:53,380
How is your girlfriend?

694
00:45:53,459 --> 00:45:55,177
I look forward
to you meeting her.

695
00:45:55,253 --> 00:45:57,972
And I look forward to your meeting
the girl you're going to marry.

696
00:45:58,047 --> 00:46:01,051
She comes from a very good family
in Delhi, beta, a very good family.

697
00:46:01,133 --> 00:46:04,512
I can marry as I choose, Mummyji.
I don't need anyone's permission.

698
00:46:04,595 --> 00:46:08,395
I presume it is your girlfriend who tills
your head with this nonsense, huh?

699
00:46:08,474 --> 00:46:10,818
A very good reason
not to marry her.

700
00:46:10,935 --> 00:46:14,030
What if I love her?
An even better reason.

701
00:46:14,105 --> 00:46:16,904
Now go and get Young Wasim to come
and get my luggage from the car.

702
00:46:16,983 --> 00:46:20,954
He cannot carry. He has a dicky back.
Wait. Your luggage?

703
00:46:21,070 --> 00:46:24,791
How long are you staying?
As long as it takes.

704
00:46:34,583 --> 00:46:37,837
Dear, you won't get anywhere
sweeping like that.

705
00:46:37,920 --> 00:46:42,016
I was in service for years.
Looked after a lovely house.

706
00:46:42,091 --> 00:46:46,392
Kept it spotless.
You need to put more pressure on the brush.

707
00:46:46,470 --> 00:46:48,643
She won't speak English.

708
00:46:48,723 --> 00:46:50,942
She's what they used to call
an untouchable.

709
00:46:51,017 --> 00:46:53,736
To a good Hindu,
even her shadow is polluted.

710
00:46:54,437 --> 00:46:55,484
Namaste-

711
00:47:00,693 --> 00:47:04,823
Where do you go every day?
ls it a woman?

712
00:47:04,905 --> 00:47:07,374
Go for a curry?
Have a bit of afters?

713
00:47:09,035 --> 00:47:10,708
No, no, no. I don't think so.

714
00:47:10,786 --> 00:47:12,288
I'm, um-

715
00:47:12,371 --> 00:47:14,123
I'm gay. Uh-

716
00:47:14,206 --> 00:47:17,585
Though nowadays,
more in theory than in practice.

717
00:47:17,668 --> 00:47:19,545
But I-I-I'll see you later.

718
00:47:43,277 --> 00:47:46,872
[Man ] The Viceroy Club was opened
by the great Lord Kitchener himself,

719
00:47:46,947 --> 00:47:50,121
and many of its fixtures have
remained unchanged since then.

720
00:47:50,201 --> 00:47:52,295
Yes, I see that.

721
00:47:52,370 --> 00:47:54,623
Perhaps you could tell me a
little about the clientele.

722
00:47:55,790 --> 00:47:59,465
Any maharajas, wealthy
widowed landowners?

723
00:47:59,543 --> 00:48:03,764
It is not the policy of this club to
divulge details of our members, madam.

724
00:48:03,839 --> 00:48:06,638
- Good morning, Your Excellency.
- Very good morning.

725
00:48:08,135 --> 00:48:09,432
Where do I sign up?

726
00:48:09,512 --> 00:48:12,265
The admission fee
is 120,000 rupees,

727
00:48:12,348 --> 00:48:16,023
and, thereafter, it will be
15,000 rupees each month.

728
00:48:16,102 --> 00:48:20,482
I wonder if I might get a little
discount, owing to my status.

729
00:48:20,564 --> 00:48:22,032
Your status, madam?

730
00:48:22,108 --> 00:48:24,736
Yes. One was rather hoping
to fly under the radar,

731
00:48:24,819 --> 00:48:26,867
but one is a member
of the royal family.

732
00:48:26,987 --> 00:48:29,536
Which member, madam?
I'm Princess Margaret.

733
00:48:31,283 --> 00:48:33,581
It is most certainly
an honor to meet you, madam.

734
00:48:33,661 --> 00:48:36,130
And may I say
how well you look,

735
00:48:36,205 --> 00:48:38,674
especially taking into account
that you died nine years ago.

736
