May I?

1440
01:45:22,037 --> 01:45:23,755
Mummyji.

1441
01:45:23,830 --> 01:45:26,800
Mummyji, do you remember
what my father used to say?

1442
01:45:26,875 --> 01:45:29,799
That nothing happens
unless first we dream.

1443
01:45:29,878 --> 01:45:33,678
And I have dreamt, Mummyji,
and like him, I have failed.

1444
01:45:33,757 --> 01:45:38,183
The Marigold Hotel is crumbling to dust,
and it turns out I can live with that.

1445
01:45:38,261 --> 01:45:41,765
But the one thing I will not do
is live without this girl.

1446
01:45:43,308 --> 01:45:46,027
This is Sunaina
Shantanu Palawar.

1447
01:45:46,937 --> 01:45:49,656
The woman I love
and wish to marry.

1448
01:45:49,731 --> 01:45:52,234
I'm very pleased to meet you, Mrs.
Kapoor.

1449
01:45:54,736 --> 01:45:57,239
No, Sonny. I forbid it.

1450
01:45:57,322 --> 01:45:59,370
I forbid this match.

1451
01:45:59,449 --> 01:46:01,827
Utterly and completely.
Do you hear me?

1452
01:46:01,910 --> 01:46:04,789
This can't happen.

1453
01:46:17,551 --> 01:46:19,349
What is he saying?

1454
01:46:19,427 --> 01:46:21,179
Um-

1455
01:46:24,349 --> 01:46:27,523
He says that he's been with this
family for as long as he can remember.

1456
01:46:31,940 --> 01:46:34,284
And that he remembers
another tight.

1457
01:46:34,359 --> 01:46:37,203
Between two young people
and their parents.

1458
01:46:44,160 --> 01:46:46,504
And he remembers the moment
when the young man...

1459
01:46:46,621 --> 01:46:50,797
stood up to his mother
and said- And said...

1460
01:46:50,876 --> 01:46:54,096
Yes, I want to marry
this woman.

1461
01:46:54,170 --> 01:46:57,765
Yes, she comes from
a different community,

1462
01:46:57,841 --> 01:47:00,936
but she's smart
and she's beautiful,

1463
01:47:02,304 --> 01:47:03,977
and I love her.

1464
01:47:09,102 --> 01:47:12,151
I don't know
who he's talking about.

1465
01:47:17,277 --> 01:47:20,998
Sunaina, I may have
no right to judge,

1466
01:47:21,072 --> 01:47:24,121
but I have a mother's right
to worry,

1467
01:47:25,535 --> 01:47:28,163
Take care of my favorite son.

1468
01:47:33,460 --> 01:47:37,215
Sorry. I'm not clear now.
Am I staying or going?

1469
01:47:37,297 --> 01:47:40,267
- Well, it depends how you read the accounts.
- The accounts?

1470
01:47:40,342 --> 01:47:43,642
It turns out the original plan
for the hotel is good.

1471
01:47:43,720 --> 01:47:47,224
It works.
Just not in the hands of a lunatic.

1472
01:47:47,307 --> 01:47:49,480
I knew that plan was good.

1473
01:47:49,559 --> 01:47:52,028
What the place needs
is money.

1474
01:47:52,103 --> 01:47:56,449
And guests, starting with the
ones that are already here.

1475
01:47:56,524 --> 01:47:59,027
Unfortunately, my investor, Mr.
Maruthi, has decided that,

1476
01:47:59,110 --> 01:48:01,454
while he greatly admires
my endeavors-

1477
01:48:02,906 --> 01:48:05,830
- He's reconsidered.
- You spoke to him?

1478
01:48:05,909 --> 01:48:09,129
So long as there's somebody
sane to help the manager.

1479
01:48:09,204 --> 01:48:11,457
No. The manager
needs no help, madam.

1480
01:48:11,539 --> 01:48:12,711
Sonny.

1481
01:48:13,291 --> 01:48:14,793
Hmm.

1482
01:48:14,876 --> 01:48:19,006
- The manager needs a little help.
- So will you stay?

1483
01:48:19,089 --> 01:48:21,842
- I'd like to.
- In the shack on the roof?

1484
01:48:22,676 --> 01:48:25,225
We have a- a double room,

1485
01:48:25,303 --> 01:48:28,022
bathroom en suite,
and a fully working door.

1486
01:48:28,098 --> 01:48:32,274
Mr. Dashwood, as you
know, has recently checked out.

1487
01:48:32,352 --> 01:48:34,901
Oh.

1488
01:48:37,607 --> 01:48:40,281
Mrs. Hardcastle,
you'll stay.

1489
01:48:40,360 --> 01:48:43,864
- On my own?
- I know you're off your game, dear.

1490
01:48:43,947 --> 01:48:46,541
Lost your confidence maybe.

1491
01:48:46,616 --> 01:48:51,372
But, you know, you are a thoroughbred.
You'll be back.

1492
01:48:53,498 --> 01:48:56,251
What about you,
Mrs. Greenslade?

1493
01:48:56,334 --> 01:48:58,007
What about me,
Mrs. Donnelly?

1494
01:48:58,086 --> 01:49:00,714
We haven't talked much,
have we? You and I.

1495
01:49:01,589 --> 01:49:03,683
My loss, evidently.

1496
01:49:04,551 --> 01:49:06,645
Will you stay?

1497
01:49:08,013 --> 01:49:10,107
I'm not sure
what I shall do.

1498
01:49:12,976 --> 01:49:17,152
Nothing here has worked out
quite as I expected.

1499
01:49:17,230 --> 01:49:19,278
Most things don't.

1500
01:49:19,399 --> 01:49:24,576
But, you know, sometimes what
happens instead is the good stuff.

1501
01:49:25,864 --> 01:49:28,287
Don't you have work
to go to in the morning?

1502
01:49:30,368 --> 01:49:32,086
Yes.

1503
01:49:33,329 --> 01:49:37,300
Now, if you'll excuse me.

1504
01:49:40,295 --> 01:49:44,971
If I can stand on my own two
feet, I'm sure you can too.

1505
01:49:46,593 --> 01:49:49,267
Who's the new
assistant manager?

1506
01:49:49,345 --> 01:49:52,019
Mr. Maruthi had me in mind.

1507
01:49:52,098 --> 01:49:54,897
You thinking of applying
for the job?

1508
01:49:58,021 --> 01:50:00,399
Oh, chair, please.

1509
01:50:07,530 --> 01:50:10,204
That's quite enough exercise
for one day.

1510
01:50:10,784 --> 01:50:12,457
Office.

1511
01:50:13,536 --> 01:50:15,209
Oh, steady.

1512
01:50:16,164 --> 01:50:18,417
Oh!

1513
01:50:35,183 --> 01:50:37,811
This is absolutely ridiculous.

1514
01:50:37,894 --> 01:50:42,024
We could be here for hours.
There's no way we'll get out of here.

1515
01:50:42,107 --> 01:50:44,201
- Well, maybe there is.
- You!

1516
01:50:45,485 --> 01:50:47,658
Can you get us
to the airport?

1517
01:50:47,737 --> 01:50:50,365
Sorry. Long way.
Sore legs, Not possible.

1518
01:50:50,448 --> 01:50:52,542
I'll give you
everything I have.

1519
01:50:53,493 --> 01:50:55,837
Okay, step right in,
let's go.

1520
01:50:55,912 --> 01:50:58,131
Can you get our cases out,
please?

1521
01:50:58,206 --> 01:51:00,675
Come on, Douglas.
Come on, Douglas, come on.

1522
01:51:00,750 --> 01:51:03,845
- Sorry, no manage people and cases.
- What?

1523
01:51:03,920 --> 01:51:07,595
It's not possible, madam.
Two persons, no cases. One person and cases.

1524
01:51:07,674 --> 01:51:11,770
Well, how about if I give you something else?
I'll give you my watch.

1525
01:51:11,845 --> 01:51:15,145
Sure. Thanks.
But still it's not possible, madam.

1526
01:51:15,223 --> 01:51:18,022
We'll get another flight. Let's go back
to the hotel and leave in the morning.

1527
01:51:18,143 --> 01:51:20,817
No. Jean, he can't do it.
You heard what he said.

1528
01:51:20,895 --> 01:51:23,523
- He can do one person and cases.
- Yeah, but-

1529
01:51:23,606 --> 01:51:27,201
Could fate ind a better way to
tell us what we need to hear?

1530
01:51:28,486 --> 01:51:32,116
- Which is what?
- That it's over.

1531
01:51:32,198 --> 01:51:34,451
That it's been over
for a long, long time.

1532
01:51:34,534 --> 01:51:37,504
This is not the time to talk about
this, Let's wait until we get home.

1533
01:51:37,579 --> 01:51:39,832
I have to go, Douglas.

1534
01:51:41,624 --> 01:51:42,750
I won't let you.

1535
01:51:42,834 --> 01:51:46,930
No. You'll come after me.

1536
01:51:47,005 --> 01:51:50,726
You'll chase me to the airport,
tell me everything will be fine.

1537
01:51:50,800 --> 01:51:52,473
But please don't.

1538
01:51:53,636 --> 01:51:55,889
Because the truth is-

1539
01:51:55,972 --> 01:51:58,896
The truth is we both deserve
more than we've had.

1540
01:52:00,685 --> 01:52:03,689
And it's just because
of your...

1541
01:52:03,771 --> 01:52:05,865
kindness and your-

1542
01:52:07,567 --> 01:52:11,913
your loyalty
that you won't admit it.

1543
01:52:17,869 --> 01:52:19,963
I'll be all right.

1544
01:52:23,333 --> 01:52:25,461
I'm turning left.

1545
01:52:30,256 --> 01:52:32,099
Good-bye, Douglas.

1546
01:52:47,148 --> 01:52:48,821
Day 51.

1547
01:52:52,904 --> 01:52:57,205
The only real failure
is the failure to try.

1548
01:52:59,035 --> 01:53:03,165
And the measure of success is how
we cope with disappointment,

1549
01:53:04,791 --> 01:53:06,668
As we always must

1550
01:53:10,797 --> 01:53:14,017
We came here and we Med

1551
01:53:14,092 --> 01:53:16,936
All of us our different ways.

1552
01:53:21,140 --> 01:53:25,316
Can we be blamed for feeling
that we are too old to change?

1553
01:53:28,690 --> 01:53:31,990
Too scared of disappointment
to start it alll again?

1554
01:53:36,322 --> 01:53:38,416
We get up 177 the morning.

1555
01:53:39,534 --> 01:53:41,628
We do our best

1556
01:53:43,997 --> 01:53:46,091
Nothing else matters.

1557
01:54:13,151 --> 01:54:16,371
You're still here.
I-I-I missed the plane.

1558
01:54:17,655 --> 01:54:20,909
What about Jean?
She didn't.

1559
01:54:23,828 --> 01:54:27,082
I had- I had quite an
interesting night actually.

1560
01:54:27,165 --> 01:54:29,839
I-I met the same, um,
taxi driver,

1561
01:54:29,917 --> 01:54:33,046
but this time I let him take
me to his brother's hotel.

1562
01:54:33,129 --> 01:54:36,633
Wh-Which turned out to be less
of a hotel and more of a-

1563
01:54:38,009 --> 01:54:41,138
more of a brothel really.

1564
01:54:41,220 --> 01:54:44,850
And they- And they gave me this
pipe, said it was apple tobacco.

1565
01:54:44,932 --> 01:54:48,857
But that's not what they called
it when I was a student.

1566
01:54:48,936 --> 01:54:51,860
So-So I made my excuses
and left.

1567
01:54:51,939 --> 01:54:55,569
Uh, I need-
I needed time to... think.

1568
01:54:58,780 --> 01:55:02,455
This city at night
is extraordinary.

1569
01:55:04,660 --> 01:55:07,914
I think the apple tobacco
helped probably,

1570
01:55:08,039 --> 01:55:10,588
I'm going to be late for work.
Right.

1571
01:55:12,752 --> 01:55:14,299
Um-

1572
01:55:15,546 --> 01:55:19,096
What time do you finish?
I get back about 5:00.

1573
01:55:20,468 --> 01:55:22,562
Teatime.
Yes.

1574
01:55:22,678 --> 01:55:26,649
How do you take it?
With a little milk.

1575
01:55:26,724 --> 01:55:28,397
All right.

1576
01:55:49,372 --> 01:55:53,377
But its also true
that the person who risks nothing...

1577
01:55:53,459 --> 01:55:57,339
does nothing, has nothing.

1578
01:56:01,175 --> 01:56:05,521
All we know about the future
is that it will be diferent.

1579
01:56:05,596 --> 01:56:07,724
Just your signature, please.

1580
01:56:10,685 --> 01:56:13,279
Thank you. Enjoy your stay.

1581
01:56:13,980 --> 01:56:16,654
Welcome. Please.

1582
01:56:19,026 --> 01:56:21,825
This is a building
of the utmost character.

1583
01:56:21,904 --> 01:56:26,660
But perhaps what
we fear is that it will be the same.

1584
01:56:30,037 --> 01:56:32,881
So we must celebrate
the changes.

1585
01:56:32,957 --> 01:56:34,504
Thank you.

1586
01:56:36,127 --> 01:56:40,553
Because, as someone once said everything
will be all right in the end.

1587
01:56:41,757 --> 01:56:46,433
And if it's not all right,
then trust me-

1588
01:56:49,348 --> 01:56:51,567
It's not yet the end.

